    req = urllib.request.Request\(

        headers={''Authorization'': ''Bearer rnd_dA90AAa3NsGoavJiSLryFaS3poHU''},

        result = json.loads\(resp.read\(\).decode\(\)\)
        status = result[''status'']
        print\(f''Attempt {i+1}: {status}''\)
        if status == ''live'':
            break
        if status in \(''deactivated'', ''build_failed'', ''update_failed'', ''canceled''\):
            print\(''Deploy failed!''\)
            print\(json.dumps\(result, indent=2\)\)
            break
")

import urllib.request, json, time

for i in range\(6\):
    time.sleep\(15\)
    req = urllib.request.Request\(
        ''https://api.render.com/v1/services/srv-d67dhhjuibrs73cj5lhg/deploys/dep-d67dkr6sb7us73e5hgs0'',
        headers={''Authorization'': ''Bearer rnd_dA90AAa3NsGoavJiSLryFaS3poHU''},
        method=''GET''
    \)
    with urllib.request.urlopen\(req\) as resp:
        result = json.loads\(resp.read\(\).decode\(\)\)
        status = result[''status'']
        print\(f''Attempt {i+1}: {status}''\)
        if status == ''live'':
            # Now try to fetch the site
            time.sleep\(5\)
            try:
                req2 = urllib.request.Request\(''https://stu-davidson-proposal.onrender.com''\)
                with urllib.request.urlopen\(req2\) as resp2:
                    content = resp2.read\(\).decode\(\)
                    print\(f''Site returned {resp2.status}, content length: {len\(content\)}''\)
                    print\(content[:200]\)
            except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:
                print\(f''Site returned HTTP {e.code}''\)
            break
        if status in \(''deactivated'', ''build_failed'', ''update_failed'', ''canceled''\):
            print\(json.dumps\(result, indent=2\)\)
            break
")
